State variables are the varibales that will be stored in the contract storage , which means they will still be stored even after the contract is executed.

there are many state variable that we can define to address the use case of the contract that we are writting.

//SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT
pragma solidity ^0.8.13;

// Write the state varibales here

uint myRent = 3000; /*int is an unsigned integer which is an alias for uint256 means that it will store values upto 256bit.and uint means it will only store non-nagative vaules. we can delare variables with less bits like uint8,uint16,uint32 based on the requirement.

contract roomRent {
// the contract logic here
}
